1.install node.js, npm
https://nodejs.org/en/

2.install angular-cli and set yarn as npm manager:
the method he used didn't work for me, so I use this one

chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ yarn global add @angular/cli
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ npm install -g @angular/cli
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ ng config -g cli.packageManager yarn

[Ref]https://blog.angular-university.io/getting-started-with-angular-setup-a-development-environment-with-yarn-the-angular-cli-setup-an-ide/
[Ref]https://www.gurustop.net/blog/2017/01/26/use-yarn-npm-with-angular-cli

3.install typescript globally:
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ npm install -g typescript
[Ref]https://blog.teamtreehouse.com/getting-started-typescript

3.clone the project
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ git clone https://github.com/simonmoreau/RevitToIFC.git
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ cd RevitToIFC 

4.install jasmine2.8 locally:
in RevitToIFC root dir:
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ npm install typescript@2.8

5.link the required dependencies:
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ sudo yarn

6.run
chenhsi@TheOtter ~ $ ng serve --open


optional:
if some thing goes wrong, before link again:
1.delete node_module dir: sudo rm -r node_module
2.delete package-lock.json: sudo rm -r package-lock.json
3.clean cache: npm cache clean --force

[Ref]https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/issues/30310
